			<span id="comment-128578580-content"><p>@Edward - the procedure for replacing the MBP hard drive is as nothing compared to the procedure needed for my 14" iBook. One case removal and you're there? The iBook needed the lower case, upper case, lower shield and upper shield removing before I could get at the HDD.</p>

<p>My advice would be just do it, but be methodical and keep track of where all the different screws came from. Also, acquaint yourself with the guides @ <a href="http://www.ifixit.com/" rel="nofollow">http://www.ifixit.com/</a> - they're very good, IMO.</p></span>
